At those passages, the Tribunal: 


 &#8226; referred to the appellant's concern about the exempt documents unfairly influencing the Tribunal's decision;
 &#8226; said it could not go into much detail about the contents of the exempt documents;
 &#8226; said the accusations in them were "unsupported"; and
 &#8226; said it would not be taking them into account but would "put them aside".
